{
  "stem": "19198.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I think I got to Heidelberg once or twice while I was there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why are you asking?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The seminary was not in Heidelberg.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The seminary was in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As far as I know, the seminary was still in existence.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I believe it got-- went out of existence in 1938 or 1939, when that type of thing was more likely to happen after Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "While in 1935, most people that I knew at all would still communicate, by 1937 there were very few people with whom I could or would communicate.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That-- that is what caused the sense of incarceration without a wall.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was this wall of-- well, the-- the-- I think it is the [NON-ENGLISH] or the-- the-- some of the very fundamentalist and exclusive sects that have the custom of shunning a person who has been excommunicated.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I learned what it meant to be shunned.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were the same people, having gone-- having grown, I'd say, at least a decade older during the two years that I was gone, because they lived in constant-- under constant pressure.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And with always new wrinkles in the kind of troubles that the government shaped for its-- for its Jewish inhabitants.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that's-- that's extremely difficult, because being a-- a born optimist, my memory has a strong prejudice against bad memories.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I-- I have forgotten most of those details, while I have not forgotten the general feeling that I've just described.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- really, nothing specific that was harmful happened.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If somebody can be in a place for six weeks and the worst possible thing that can happen to him was to have his-- not to have his passport on him, you can draw your conclusion.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nothing dramatic happened in those six weeks.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
